    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320.2–AA/9–2051: Despatch</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Lebanon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d492fn1">Drafted by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BDC1"
                            >Bergus</persName>; sent also to Damascus, Cairo, Baghdad, Amman, Tel
                        Aviv, Jidda, Paris, and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/> No. 142</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-20">September 20,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Preliminary Discussion of <gloss target="#t_UNRWAPNE1"
                        >UNRWA</gloss>’s (<gloss target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss>’s) Three-Year
                    Reintegration Program with Lebanese Minister of Foreign Affairs</p>
                <p>On September 12, 1951, the Honorable <persName corresp="#p_BJB2">John B.
                        Blandford</persName>, Director of <gloss target="#t_UNRWAPNE1">UNRWA</gloss>
                        (<gloss target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss>), met with H. E. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHC1">Charles Helou</persName>, Lebanese Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs. A memorandum of that conversation, prepared by Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BJB2">Blandford</persName>, is enclosed.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d492fn2">Not printed</note>
                </p>
                <p>During the conversation Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BJB2">Blandford</persName>
                    handed to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Helou</persName> a copy of the outline
                    of the Agency’s proposal for a three-year reintegration program, which is
                    attached as Enclosure No. 2.<note n="2" xml:id="d492fn3">Not printed.</note>
                    This proposal, which has received the approbation of the Advisory Commission,
                    will be discussed by the Director with the Near East Governments during his
                    present second round of visits.</p>
                <p>The salient points of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Helou</persName>’s remarks
                    were: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Although Lebanon can undertake nothing more than symbolic
                            reintegration on her own overcrowded territory, she is prepared to
                            render strong political support to <gloss target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss>.
                            If necessary and desirable, Lebanon will take the initiative in
                            obtaining Arab League approval for the program.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Helou</persName> suggested that in
                            conversations with Arab Governments, particularly Syria, <gloss
                                target="#t_PRA1">PRA</gloss> should stress the financial side of its
                            program, particularly the immediate large local expenditures which would
                            result.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The role of the <gloss target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss> in these negotiations was
                    also discussed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John H. Bruins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
